@neuro_rish for many semi-structured tasks you can indeed get away with suction or parallel jaw grippers, but the world is made by humans assuming human hands, and many things are out of reach of those, and it'll be really neat to have a robotic version

@JJ_Hepboin that hand has a nice form factor, but it is very expensive and requires more or less a dedicated maintenance engineer to continually maintain/fix it; so I wouldn't count that as a good enough hand in its current state

I believe ultimately most of the challenges towards value creation will be in the AI.  But setting that aside, what's the hardest R&D ahead for hardware?  

I am gonna say "human-level hands".  But I think it's feasible, and I for one can't wait to get to work with some of those https://t.co/JxnszWSbrU
